exactInputSingleWithSecondaryFee((addres.details: Takes a fee on the input token by taking a cut from the `amountIn`, of the size of the fee amount, after doing the swapThe developer does not need to modify the `amountIn`This swap has only one hopEmits a `FeeTaken` event for each fee recipientIt is possible that the amountIn specified is greater than the actual amountIn required.      This can happen when there is low liquidity in the pool.      The swap needs to execute before the fee can be calculated and transferred to fee recipients.

params.secondaryFees: The details of the secondary fee(s)

exactInputWithSecondaryFee((address,uint.details: Takes a fee on the input token by taking a cut from the `amountIn`, of the size of the fee amount, after doing the swapThe developer does not need to modify the `amountIn`This swap has multiple hopsEmits a `FeeTaken` event for each fee recipientIt is possible that the amountIn specified is greater than the actual amountIn required.      This can happen when there is low liquidity in the pool.      The swap needs to execute before the fee can be calculated and transferred to fee recipients.

params.secondaryFees: The details of the secondary fee(s)

exactOutputSingleWithSecondaryFee((addre.details: Takes a fee on the input token after the swap has executed, from the amount used to pay for the swapThe developer should calculate the fee amount and increase the `swapParams.amountInMaximum` by that amountThis swap has only one hopEmits a `FeeTaken` event for each fee recipient.

params.secondaryFees: The details of the secondary fee(s)

returns.amountIn: The amount of `tokenIn` swapped, inclusive of the fee

exactOutputWithSecondaryFee((address,uin.details: Takes a fee on the input token after the swap has executed, from the amount used to pay for the swapThe developer should calculate the fee amount and increase the `swapParams.amountInMaximum` by that amountThis swap has multiple hopsEmits a `FeeTaken` event for each fee recipient

params.secondaryFees: The details of the secondary fee(s)

returns.amountIn: The amount of `tokenIn` swapped, inclusive of the fee

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params.data: The calldata for each call to be made
The calldata for each call to be made

returns._0: results The results from each call

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

unwrapNativeToken(uint256).details: Should be used within a multicall function when the output token is intended to be native IMX.      This is to atomically swap and unwrap the resulting tokens in a single transaction.
